.TH "msi_capability_init" 9 "msi_capability_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
msi_capability_init \- configure device's MSI capability structure
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" msi_capability_init
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "int nvec "  ","
.BI "struct irq_affinity *affd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
pointer to the pci_dev data structure of MSI device function
.IP "nvec" 12
number of interrupts to allocate
.IP "affd" 12
description of automatic IRQ affinity assignments (may be NULL)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Setup the MSI capability structure of the device with the requested
number of interrupts.  A return value of zero indicates the successful
setup of an entry with the new MSI IRQ.  A negative return value indicates
an error, and a positive return value indicates the number of interrupts
which could have been allocated.
